{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos1.erdos_1 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos1.erdos_1.","id":"vf_40af91d61559aa1d","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. If $A\\subseteq \\{1,\\ldots,N\\}$ with $\\lvert A\\rvert=n$ is such that the subset sums $\\sum_{a\\in S}a$ are distinct for all $S\\subseteq A$ then\\[N \\gg 2^{n}.\\] Current best: The trivial lower bound is $N \\gg 2^{n}/n$, since all $2^n$ distinct subset sums must lie in $[0,Nn)$. Erd\\H{o}s and Moser \\cite{Er56} proved\\[ N\\geq (\\tfrac{1}{4}-o(1))\\frac{2^n}{\\sqrt{n}}.\\](In \\cite{Er85c} Erd\\H{o}s offered \\$100 for any improvement of the constant $1/4$ here.)  A number of improvements of the constant have been given (see \\cite{St23} for a history), with the current record $\\sqrt{2/\\pi}$ first proved in unpublished work of Elkies and Gleason. Two proofs achieving this constant are provided by Dubroff, Fox, and Xu \\cite{DFX21}, who in fact prove the exact bound $N\\geq \\binom{n}{\\lfloor n/2\\rfloor}$. Prize: $500. OEIS: A276661. Tags: additive combinatorics, number theory.","id":"vf_7746daa976a29829","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"attempted via frontier 'sidon/B2' (transfer_strength=partial) -> no_progress","claimed_status":"draft","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_6c10fd3dd5c155b4","kind":"dead_end","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"sidon/B2","method_families":[],"named_obstructions":[],"related_problems":[],"remaining_obligations":[],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_6c10fd3dd5c155b4","trust":"signed"}],"activity_types":["attempt"],"attempt_count":1,"banked_attempt_count":1,"commits":[{"commit":"121807e20b06eb8148f594dfe13e440181252b0f","repository":"erdos_frontier","source_root":"sha256:210e6e1b2ca1